description: A large reactor powered freighter with zero frills. Some claim the Edelweiss was a cheaply thrown together imitation of the Ryokka CR-43, built to cash in on the colony rush and pushed into production as soon as Testudo's executives got their hands on Ryokka's early design concepts.
